Function return:
The return statement that can be used to return the value to function call
Example:
Function a(aa ,bb){
return aa+bb;
}
let n1=parseFloat(prompt(“enter a number:”) 
let n2=parseFloat(prompt(“enter a number:”) 
//Calling a function
let result = a(n1,n2);
//display the result
console.log(“The sum is: ”+result)
Anomymous functions:
A Function without name ,After we create a function without name and we assign it to a variable
Ex:
Sum=function(n1,n2)
let r = n1+n2
return r 
}
Console.log(sum(8,9))
Topic:Functions
A Function is a reusable block of code
It can be called any where in the Program
Reusable code:using an existing code without writing it ever we need
You can use the same code with different arguments to get the results
JS:
KeyWord=function
( )
Parameters=values which are declared inside ( )
While defining a functions
Arguments=values which are passed through the parameters


Syntax:
Unit set of functions which are used to create the program
Function function_name(){
-----`block of code’
}
function_name()to print
Ex:
<script>
        function greet(){
            console.log("Hello World")
        }
        greet()
    </script>
Output:
Hello World
Ex:
<script>
        function greet(){
            console.log("Hello World")
        }
        greet()
        console,log("Hello India")
        greet()
    </script>
Output:
Hello World
Hello India
Ex:Function with Parameters
//Function with parameters
        function g(name){
            console.log("hello "+name)
        }
        let name=prompt("Enter your name:")
        g(name)
Output:
Enter your name: sita
Hello sita
Ex: write a function to add two numbers 
function add(a,b){
            console.log(a+b)
        }
        let a=prompt("Enter the a:")
        let b=prompt("Enter the b:")
        add(a,b)
Output:
Enter the a:3
Enter the b:4
7
Function return:
The return statement that can be used to return the value to function call
Example:
Function a(aa ,bb){
return aa+bb;
}
let n1=parseFloat(prompt(“enter a number:”) 
let n2=parseFloat(prompt(“enter a number:”) 
//Calling a function
let result = a(n1,n2);
//display the result
console.log(“The sum is: ”+result)
Anomymous functions:
A Function without name ,After we create a function without name and we assign it to a variable
Ex:
Sum=function(n1,n2)
let r = n1+n2
return r 
}
Console.log(sum(8,9))
